<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 07 at 7:40AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow squalls possible this afternoon into early this evening...
A strong cold front is expected to move from north to south through
the region during the afternoon and evening hours today.
A band of snow, gusty winds and falling temperatures is expected to
accompany the cold front.
There is the potential for snow squalls along the cold front, which
could result in a brief period of heavy snowfall, whiteout
conditions and a flash freeze, as the colder air moves into the
region. If these conditions develop, snow squall warnings could be
issued.
This line of heavy snow showers and snow squalls should move south
of the Canadian border around 3 PM, and should continue south
through the evening, reaching a line from Lewistown to Helena
around 9 PM.
Those traveling later this afternoon and early this evening should
listen for updates on this situation.</description>
